  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed the <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> pepper strips </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin </strong>to the pan</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>add a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>gluten free linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the linguine for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite, then drain it, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>meat-free chick'n </strong>to the pan with the vegetables and cook for 4-6 min further or until warmed through and starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meat-free chick'n is starting to brown, add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> and cook for a final 4-5 min further or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> Cajun-style meat-free chick'n & pepper gluten free linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Cajun-style meat-free chick'n & pepper gluten free linguine</strong> and season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
